      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are often designed to protect domestic industries by making imported goods more expensive, but this protection frequently comes at the cost of higher prices for consumers. While businesses may benefit from reduced foreign competition, the resulting inflation and reduced purchasing power often outweigh these gains for the general public. Ultimately, the economic impact depends on which specific industries are targeted and the broader global trade context.",
